						<summary>

						<p>North base of the verandah in the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Mantrapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chaḍaiyavarmaṉ Sundarapāṇḍya: year 14: 1263 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription furnishes the details of date viz., year 14, Siṁha śu 3, Wednesday, Hasta-nakshatra which may be equated with 1263 A.D., August 8, f.d.n. ·34.</p>						

						<p>This incomplete record stops with the mention of the ancient geographical divisions to which [Kēraḷa*]kulāśaṉich-chaturvēdimaṅgalam belonged. It is stated to have been included in Puṟaṅkarambai-nāḍu in Rājēndraśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
